SETUP & CONFIGURATION

git init - initialize a new Git repository

git clone - clone a repository into a new directory

git config - get and set repository or global options

git help - display help information about git

BASIC SNAPSHOTTING

git add - add file contents to the staging area

git status - shows working tree status

git commit - record changes to the repository

git reset - reset current HEAD to specified state

git rm - remove files from working tree & index

git mv - move or rename a file, directory or symlink

git ls-files - shows staging files.

Branching & Merging

git branch - list, create, or delete branches

git checkout - switch branches or restore files

git merge - join two or more development histories

git rebase - reapply commits on top of another base tip

git tag - create, list, delete or verify tags

git stash - stash changes in a dirty working directory

Sharing & Updating

git fetch - download objects & refs from repo

git pull - fetch & integrate with another repo

git push - update remote refs & objects

git remote - manage set of tracked repos

Inspection & Comparison

git log - show commit logs

git diff - show changes b/w commits, commit & tree

git show - show various types of objects/files in committed area

git blame - show who changed what line in a file.
